<td id="LC1" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">2 . take around 10,000 640x480 pictures .

<td id="LC2" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">i downloaded a trial version of computer associates ez firewall and antivirus and fell in love with a computer security system all over again .
<td id="LC3" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">the wrt54g plus the hga7t is a perfect solution if you need wireless coverage in a wider area or for a hard-walled house as was my case .

<td id="LC4" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">i dont especially like how music files are unstructured ; basically they are just dumped into one folder with no organization , like you might have in windows explorer folders and subfolders .
<td id="LC5" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">i was using the cheapie pail ... and it worked ok until the opening device fell apart .
<td id="LC6" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">you can manage your profile , change the contrast of backlight , make different type of display , either list or tabbed .
<td id="LC7" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">11 ) minimal pause between songs - less than that on other devices - good achievement for a hard-drive based player

<td id="LC8" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">from the internet , woodworking books , local stores and personal opinions the hitachi m12v 3-1 / 4 hp router time and time again came up to be the router of choice or best for its price .

<td id="LC9" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">i loved this product when i first got it - great sound , easy to use ( even though i agree that the software was n't the best ) and held enough songs to suit any mood .
<td id="LC10" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">whether you are using disposable or cloth diapers , this is the truly the only diaper pail to get !
<td id="LC11" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">takes excellent photos .
<td id="LC12" class="blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line">it 's easy enough to pop it open to see what song you 're listening to .
